            . I had been to dinner, and on my return, between two and three o'clock, as I was crossing Long-acre, I saw the prisoner cutting off this apron; I came over to him, and he made the last cut with his knife just as I got over to him - he turned round, and walked off- I followed and took him.</p>
               <p>
            
